HEADWORD: Ward-corn
<hw>Ward"-corn`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ward</ets> +
F. <ets>corne</ets> horn, L. <ets>cornu</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng.
Law)</fld> <def>The duty of keeping watch and ward (see the Note under
<er>Watch</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 1) with a horn to be blown upon any
occasion of surprise.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

